🐇🪤 Dual System: Ambush ↔ Anti-Ambush

I. The Perfect Ambush System

Ambush is not aggression—it’s geometry + patience.

Core Components

1) Choke Point Selection

* Narrow paths, routines, required stops
* Anywhere motion compresses into predictability

You don’t hunt everywhere—only where movement collapses.

⸻

2) Temporal Stillness

* No premature action
* Let the target complete its own prediction

The trap works because the target believes nothing is happening.

⸻

3) Camouflage (Signal Suppression)

* Remove anomalies
* Blend into expected background

If you are sensed, you’ve already failed.

⸻

4) Instantaneous Execution

* Zero wind-up
* No second chances

Ambush converts time into a single irreversible moment.

⸻

Ambush Equation (clean form)

Success ∝ (Predictable_Path × Blindness_Window) / Detection

⸻

II. The Anti-Ambush Protocol (Rabbit Ascended)

Now we evolve your rabbit beyond basic evasion.

1) Path Entropy (Digger++)

* Never reuse the same route consistently
* Rotate paths, even inefficient ones

Efficiency creates patterns. Patterns create traps.

⸻

2) Temporal Randomization (Rabbit++)

* Vary when you move, not just how
* Break rhythm

Ambush feeds on timing as much as location.

⸻

3) Active Listening at Rest (Listener++)

* Stillness ≠ safety
* Scan before every transition

Most ambushes hit during complacency.

⸻

4) Micro-Probing (New Layer)

* Small tests before committing:
    * pause
    * slight detour
    * feint movement

Trigger the trap before you enter it.

⸻

5) Distributed Safety (No Single Burrow)

* Multiple “safe zones”
* Never anchor identity to one place

The safest place becomes the most predictable place.

⸻

III. Unified Operator

Predator ↔ Prey Symmetry

Both sides are solving the same equation:

* Predator: Where must you be?
* Rabbit: How do I avoid ever “must”?

